41/******************************************************************************
42 * misc
43 *****************************************************************************/
44static u32
45nvkm_clk_adjust(struct nvkm_clk *clk, bool adjust,
46 u8 pstate, u8 domain, u32 input)
47{
48 struct nvkm_bios *bios = clk->subdev.device->bios;
49 struct nvbios_boostE boostE;
50 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
51 u16 data;
52
53 data = nvbios_boostEm(bios, pstate, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &boostE);
54 if (data) {
55 struct nvbios_boostS boostS;
56 u8 idx = 0, sver, shdr;
57 u16 subd;
58
59 input = max(boostE.min, input);
60 input = min(boostE.max, input);
61 do {
62 sver = ver;
63 shdr = hdr;
64 subd = nvbios_boostSp(bios, idx++, data, &sver, &shdr,
65 cnt, len, &boostS);
66 if (subd && boostS.domain == domain) {
67 if (adjust)
68 input = input * boostS.percent / 100;
69 input = max(boostS.min, input);
70 input = min(boostS.max, input);
71 break;
72 }
73 } while (subd);
74 }
75
76 return input;
77}
78
79/******************************************************************************
80 * C-States
81 *****************************************************************************/
82static int
83nvkm_cstate_prog(struct nvkm_clk *clk, struct nvkm_pstate *pstate, int cstatei)
84{
85 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->subdev;
86 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
87 struct nvkm_therm *therm = device->therm;
88 struct nvkm_volt *volt = device->volt;
89 struct nvkm_cstate *cstate;
90 int ret;
91
92 if (!list_empty(&pstate->list)) {
93 cstate = list_entry(pstate->list.prev, typeof(*cstate), head);
94 } else {
95 cstate = &pstate->base;
96 }
97
98 if (therm) {
99 ret = nvkm_therm_cstate(therm, pstate->fanspeed, +1);
100 if (ret && ret != -ENODEV) {
101 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to raise fan speed: %d\n", ret);
102 return ret;
103 }
104 }
105
106 if (volt) {
107 ret = nvkm_volt_set_id(volt, cstate->voltage, +1);
108 if (ret && ret != -ENODEV) {
109 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to raise voltage: %d\n", ret);
110 return ret;
111 }
112 }
113
114 ret = clk->func->calc(clk, cstate);
115 if (ret == 0) {
116 ret = clk->func->prog(clk);
117 clk->func->tidy(clk);
118 }
119
120 if (volt) {
121 ret = nvkm_volt_set_id(volt, cstate->voltage, -1);
122 if (ret && ret != -ENODEV)
123 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to lower voltage: %d\n", ret);
124 }
125
126 if (therm) {
127 ret = nvkm_therm_cstate(therm, pstate->fanspeed, -1);
128 if (ret && ret != -ENODEV)
129 nvkm_error(subdev, "failed to lower fan speed: %d\n", ret);
130 }
131
132 return ret;
133}
134
135static void
136nvkm_cstate_del(struct nvkm_cstate *cstate)
137{
138 list_del(&cstate->head);
139 kfree(cstate);
140}
141
142static int
143nvkm_cstate_new(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int idx, struct nvkm_pstate *pstate)
144{
145 struct nvkm_bios *bios = clk->subdev.device->bios;
146 const struct nvkm_domain *domain = clk->domains;
147 struct nvkm_cstate *cstate = NULL;
148 struct nvbios_cstepX cstepX;
149 u8 ver, hdr;
150 u16 data;
151
152 data = nvbios_cstepXp(bios, idx, &ver, &hdr, &cstepX);
153 if (!data)
154 return -ENOENT;
155
156 cstate = kzalloc(sizeof(*cstate), GFP_KERNEL);
157 if (!cstate)
158 return -ENOMEM;
159
160 *cstate = pstate->base;
161 cstate->voltage = cstepX.voltage;
162
163 while (domain && domain->name != nv_clk_src_max) {
164 if (domain->flags & NVKM_CLK_DOM_FLAG_CORE) {
165 u32 freq = nvkm_clk_adjust(clk, true, pstate->pstate,
166 domain->bios, cstepX.freq);
167 cstate->domain[domain->name] = freq;
168 }
169 domain++;
170 }
171
172 list_add(&cstate->head, &pstate->list);
173 return 0;
174}
175
176/******************************************************************************
177 * P-States
178 *****************************************************************************/
179static int
180nvkm_pstate_prog(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int pstatei)
181{
182 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->subdev;
183 struct nvkm_ram *ram = subdev->device->fb->ram;
184 struct nvkm_pstate *pstate;
185 int ret, idx = 0;
186
187 list_for_each_entry(pstate, &clk->states, head) {
188 if (idx++ == pstatei)
189 break;
190 }
191
192 nvkm_debug(subdev, "setting performance state %d\n", pstatei);
193 clk->pstate = pstatei;
194
195 if (ram && ram->func->calc) {
196 int khz = pstate->base.domain[nv_clk_src_mem];
197 do {
198 ret = ram->func->calc(ram, khz);
199 if (ret == 0)
200 ret = ram->func->prog(ram);
201 } while (ret > 0);
202 ram->func->tidy(ram);
203 }
204
205 return nvkm_cstate_prog(clk, pstate, 0);
206}
207
208static void
209nvkm_pstate_work(struct work_struct *work)
210{
211 struct nvkm_clk *clk = container_of(work, typeof(*clk), work);
212 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->subdev;
213 int pstate;
214
215 spin_lock(&clk->lock);
216 if (!atomic_xchg(&clk->waiting, 0)) {
217 spin_unlock(&clk->lock);
218 return;
219 }
220
221 clk->pwrsrc = power_supply_is_system_supplied();
222
223 nvkm_trace(subdev, "P %d PWR %d U(AC) %d U(DC) %d A %d T %d D %d\n",
224 clk->pstate, clk->pwrsrc, clk->ustate_ac, clk->ustate_dc,
225 clk->astate, clk->tstate, clk->dstate);
226
227 pstate = clk->pwrsrc ? clk->ustate_ac : clk->ustate_dc;
228 if (clk->state_nr && pstate != -1) {
229 pstate = (pstate < 0) ? clk->astate : pstate;
230 pstate = min(pstate, clk->state_nr - 1 + clk->tstate);
231 pstate = max(pstate, clk->dstate);
232 } else {
233 pstate = clk->pstate = -1;
234 }
235
236 nvkm_trace(subdev, "-> %d\n", pstate);
237 if (pstate != clk->pstate) {
238 int ret = nvkm_pstate_prog(clk, pstate);
239 if (ret) {
240 nvkm_error(subdev, "error setting pstate %d: %d\n",
241 pstate, ret);
242 }
243 }
244
245#ifdef __NetBSD__
246 DRM_SPIN_WAKEUP_ALL(&clk->wait, &clk->lock);
247#else
248 wake_up_all(&clk->wait);
249#endif
250 spin_unlock(&clk->lock);
251 nvkm_notify_get(&clk->pwrsrc_ntfy);
252}
253
254static int
255nvkm_pstate_calc(struct nvkm_clk *clk, bool wait)
256{
257 atomic_set(&clk->waiting, 1);
258 schedule_work(&clk->work);
259 if (wait) {
260#ifdef __NetBSD__
261 if (cold) {
262 unsigned timo = 1000;
263 while (timo --> 0) {
264 if (atomic_read(&clk->waiting))
265 return 0;
266 DELAY(100);
267 }
268 return -ETIMEDOUT;
269 }
270 int ret;
271 spin_lock(&clk->lock);
272 DRM_SPIN_WAIT_NOINTR_UNTIL(ret, &clk->wait, &clk->lock,
273 !atomic_read(&clk->waiting));
274 spin_unlock(&clk->lock);
275 KASSERT(ret == 0);
276#else
277 wait_event(clk->wait, !atomic_read(&clk->waiting));
278#endif
279 }
280 return 0;
281}
282
283static void
284nvkm_pstate_info(struct nvkm_clk *clk, struct nvkm_pstate *pstate)
285{
286 const struct nvkm_domain *clock = clk->domains - 1;
287 struct nvkm_cstate *cstate;
288 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->subdev;
289 char info[3][32] = { "", "", "" };
290 char name[4] = "--";
291 int i = -1;
292
293 if (pstate->pstate != 0xff)
294 snprintf(name, sizeof(name), "%02x", pstate->pstate);
295
296 while ((++clock)->name != nv_clk_src_max) {
297 u32 lo = pstate->base.domain[clock->name];
298 u32 hi = lo;
299 if (hi == 0)
300 continue;
301
302 nvkm_debug(subdev, "%02x: %10d KHz\n", clock->name, lo);
303 list_for_each_entry(cstate, &pstate->list, head) {
304 u32 freq = cstate->domain[clock->name];
305 lo = min(lo, freq);
306 hi = max(hi, freq);
307 nvkm_debug(subdev, "%10d KHz\n", freq);
308 }
309
310 if (clock->mname && ++i < ARRAY_SIZE(info)) {
311 lo /= clock->mdiv;
312 hi /= clock->mdiv;
313 if (lo == hi) {
314 snprintf(info[i], sizeof(info[i]), "%s %d MHz",
315 clock->mname, lo);
316 } else {
317 snprintf(info[i], sizeof(info[i]),
318 "%s %d-%d MHz", clock->mname, lo, hi);
319 }
320 }
321 }
322
323 nvkm_debug(subdev, "%s: %s %s %s\n", name, info[0], info[1], info[2]);
324}
325
326static void
327nvkm_pstate_del(struct nvkm_pstate *pstate)
328{
329 struct nvkm_cstate *cstate, *temp;
330
331 list_for_each_entry_safe(cstate, temp, &pstate->list, head) {
332 nvkm_cstate_del(cstate);
333 }
334
335 list_del(&pstate->head);
336 kfree(pstate);
337}
338
339static int
340nvkm_pstate_new(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int idx)
341{
342 struct nvkm_bios *bios = clk->subdev.device->bios;
343 const struct nvkm_domain *domain = clk->domains - 1;
344 struct nvkm_pstate *pstate;
345 struct nvkm_cstate *cstate;
346 struct nvbios_cstepE cstepE;
347 struct nvbios_perfE perfE;
348 u8 ver, hdr, cnt, len;
349 u16 data;
350
351 data = nvbios_perfEp(bios, idx, &ver, &hdr, &cnt, &len, &perfE);
352 if (!data)
353 return -EINVAL;
354 if (perfE.pstate == 0xff)
355 return 0;
356
357 pstate = kzalloc(sizeof(*pstate), GFP_KERNEL);
358 cstate = &pstate->base;
359 if (!pstate)
360 return -ENOMEM;
361
362 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&pstate->list);
363
364 pstate->pstate = perfE.pstate;
365 pstate->fanspeed = perfE.fanspeed;
366 cstate->voltage = perfE.voltage;
367 cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_core] = perfE.core;
368 cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_shader] = perfE.shader;
369 cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_mem] = perfE.memory;
370 cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_vdec] = perfE.vdec;
371 cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_dom6] = perfE.disp;
372
373 while (ver >= 0x40 && (++domain)->name != nv_clk_src_max) {
374 struct nvbios_perfS perfS;
375 u8 sver = ver, shdr = hdr;
376 u32 perfSe = nvbios_perfSp(bios, data, domain->bios,
377 &sver, &shdr, cnt, len, &perfS);
378 if (perfSe == 0 || sver != 0x40)
379 continue;
380
381 if (domain->flags & NVKM_CLK_DOM_FLAG_CORE) {
382 perfS.v40.freq = nvkm_clk_adjust(clk, false,
383 pstate->pstate,
384 domain->bios,
385 perfS.v40.freq);
386 }
387
388 cstate->domain[domain->name] = perfS.v40.freq;
389 }
390
391 data = nvbios_cstepEm(bios, pstate->pstate, &ver, &hdr, &cstepE);
392 if (data) {
393 int idx = cstepE.index;
394 do {
395 nvkm_cstate_new(clk, idx, pstate);
396 } while(idx--);
397 }
398
399 nvkm_pstate_info(clk, pstate);
400 list_add_tail(&pstate->head, &clk->states);
401 clk->state_nr++;
402 return 0;
403}
404
405/******************************************************************************
406 * Adjustment triggers
407 *****************************************************************************/
408static int
409nvkm_clk_ustate_update(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int req)
410{
411 struct nvkm_pstate *pstate;
412 int i = 0;
413
414 if (!clk->allow_reclock)
415 return -ENOSYS;
416
417 if (req != -1 && req != -2) {
418 list_for_each_entry(pstate, &clk->states, head) {
419 if (pstate->pstate == req)
420 break;
421 i++;
422 }
423
424 if (pstate->pstate != req)
425 return -EINVAL;
426 req = i;
427 }
428
429 return req + 2;
430}
431
432static int
433nvkm_clk_nstate(struct nvkm_clk *clk, const char *mode, int arglen)
434{
435 int ret = 1;
436
437 if (clk->allow_reclock && !strncasecmpz(mode, "auto", arglen))
438 return -2;
439
440 if (strncasecmpz(mode, "disabled", arglen)) {
441 char *m = kstrndup(mode, arglen, GFP_KERNEL);
442 long v;
443
444 if (!kstrtol(m, 0, &v)) {
445 ret = nvkm_clk_ustate_update(clk, v);
446 if (ret < 0)
447 ret = 1;
448 }
449 kfree(m);
450 }
451
452 return ret - 2;
453}
454
455int
456nvkm_clk_ustate(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int req, int pwr)
457{
458 int ret = nvkm_clk_ustate_update(clk, req);
459 if (ret >= 0) {
460 if (ret -= 2, pwr) clk->ustate_ac = ret;
461 else clk->ustate_dc = ret;
462 return nvkm_pstate_calc(clk, true);
463 }
464 return ret;
465}
466
467int
468nvkm_clk_astate(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int req, int rel, bool wait)
469{
470 if (!rel) clk->astate = req;
471 if ( rel) clk->astate += rel;
472 clk->astate = min(clk->astate, clk->state_nr - 1);
473 clk->astate = max(clk->astate, 0);
474 return nvkm_pstate_calc(clk, wait);
475}
476
477int
478nvkm_clk_tstate(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int req, int rel)
479{
480 if (!rel) clk->tstate = req;
481 if ( rel) clk->tstate += rel;
482 clk->tstate = min(clk->tstate, 0);
483 clk->tstate = max(clk->tstate, -(clk->state_nr - 1));
484 return nvkm_pstate_calc(clk, true);
485}
486
487int
488nvkm_clk_dstate(struct nvkm_clk *clk, int req, int rel)
489{
490 if (!rel) clk->dstate = req;
491 if ( rel) clk->dstate += rel;
492 clk->dstate = min(clk->dstate, clk->state_nr - 1);
493 clk->dstate = max(clk->dstate, 0);
494 return nvkm_pstate_calc(clk, true);
495}
496
497static int
498nvkm_clk_pwrsrc(struct nvkm_notify *notify)
499{
500 struct nvkm_clk *clk =
501 container_of(notify, typeof(*clk), pwrsrc_ntfy);
502 nvkm_pstate_calc(clk, false);
503 return NVKM_NOTIFY_DROP;
504}

506/******************************************************************************
507 * subdev base class implementation
508 *****************************************************************************/
509
510int
511nvkm_clk_read(struct nvkm_clk *clk, enum nv_clk_src src)
512{
513 return clk->func->read(clk, src);
514}
515
516static int
517nvkm_clk_fini(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, bool suspend)
518{
519 struct nvkm_clk *clk = nvkm_clk(subdev);
520 nvkm_notify_put(&clk->pwrsrc_ntfy);
521 flush_work(&clk->work);
522 if (clk->func->fini)
523 clk->func->fini(clk);
524 return 0;
525}
526
527static int
528nvkm_clk_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
529{
530 struct nvkm_clk *clk = nvkm_clk(subdev);
531 const struct nvkm_domain *clock = clk->domains;
532 int ret;
533
534 memset(&clk->bstate, 0x00, sizeof(clk->bstate));
535 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&clk->bstate.list);
536 clk->bstate.pstate = 0xff;
537
538 while (clock->name != nv_clk_src_max) {
539 ret = nvkm_clk_read(clk, clock->name);
540 if (ret < 0) {
541 nvkm_error(subdev, "%02x freq unknown\n", clock->name);
542 return ret;
543 }
544 clk->bstate.base.domain[clock->name] = ret;
545 clock++;
546 }
547
548 nvkm_pstate_info(clk, &clk->bstate);
549
550 if (clk->func->init)
551 return clk->func->init(clk);
552
553 clk->astate = clk->state_nr - 1;
554 clk->tstate = 0;
555 clk->dstate = 0;
556 clk->pstate = -1;
557 nvkm_pstate_calc(clk, true);
558 return 0;
559}
560
561static void *
562nvkm_clk_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
563{
564 struct nvkm_clk *clk = nvkm_clk(subdev);
565 struct nvkm_pstate *pstate, *temp;
566
567 nvkm_notify_fini(&clk->pwrsrc_ntfy);
568
569 /* Early return if the pstates have been provided statically */
570 if (clk->func->pstates)
571 return clk;
572
573 list_for_each_entry_safe(pstate, temp, &clk->states, head) {
574 nvkm_pstate_del(pstate);
575 }
576
577#ifdef __NetBSD__
578 DRM_DESTROY_WAITQUEUE(&clk->wait);
579 spin_lock_destroy(&clk->lock);
580#endif
581
582 return clk;
583}
584
585static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
586nvkm_clk = {
587 .dtor = nvkm_clk_dtor,
588 .init = nvkm_clk_init,
589 .fini = nvkm_clk_fini,
590};
591
592int
593nvkm_clk_ctor(const struct nvkm_clk_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
594 int index, bool allow_reclock, struct nvkm_clk *clk)
595{
596 int ret, idx, arglen;
597 const char *mode;
598
599 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_clk, device, index, 0, &clk->subdev);
600 clk->func = func;
601 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&clk->states);
602 clk->domains = func->domains;
603 clk->ustate_ac = -1;
604 clk->ustate_dc = -1;
605 clk->allow_reclock = allow_reclock;
606
607 INIT_WORK(&clk->work, nvkm_pstate_work);
608#ifdef __NetBSD__
609 spin_lock_init(&clk->lock);
610 DRM_INIT_WAITQUEUE(&clk->wait, "nvclk");
611#else
612 init_waitqueue_head(&clk->wait);
613#endif
614 atomic_set(&clk->waiting, 0);
615
616 /* If no pstates are provided, try and fetch them from the BIOS */
617 if (!func->pstates) {
618 idx = 0;
619 do {
620 ret = nvkm_pstate_new(clk, idx++);
621 } while (ret == 0);
622 } else {
623 for (idx = 0; idx < func->nr_pstates; idx++)
624 list_add_tail(&func->pstates[idx].head, &clk->states);
625 clk->state_nr = func->nr_pstates;
626 }
627
628 ret = nvkm_notify_init(NULL, &device->event, nvkm_clk_pwrsrc, true,
629 NULL, 0, 0, &clk->pwrsrc_ntfy);
630 if (ret)
631 return ret;
632
633 mode = nvkm_stropt(device->cfgopt, "NvClkMode", &arglen);
634 if (mode) {
635 clk->ustate_ac = nvkm_clk_nstate(clk, mode, arglen);
636 clk->ustate_dc = nvkm_clk_nstate(clk, mode, arglen);
637 }
638
639 mode = nvkm_stropt(device->cfgopt, "NvClkModeAC", &arglen);
640 if (mode)
641 clk->ustate_ac = nvkm_clk_nstate(clk, mode, arglen);
642
643 mode = nvkm_stropt(device->cfgopt, "NvClkModeDC", &arglen);
644 if (mode)
645 clk->ustate_dc = nvkm_clk_nstate(clk, mode, arglen);
646
647 return 0;
648}
649
650int
651nvkm_clk_new_(const struct nvkm_clk_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
652 int index, bool allow_reclock, struct nvkm_clk **pclk)
653{
654 if (!(*pclk = kzalloc(sizeof(**pclk), GFP_KERNEL)))
655 return -ENOMEM;
656 return nvkm_clk_ctor(func, device, index, allow_reclock, *pclk);
657}
